[{"id":"VR596881","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR596879.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following must be true?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR596881_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<p>The following questions are based on the graph provided, which shows the combinations of donuts and cups of coffee that the country of Deetopia could produce using its currently available resources.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows the graph of a curve in the first quadrant of a coordinate plane. The horizontal axis is labeled “Donuts,” and the numbers 0 through 24, in increments of 6, are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Cups of Coffee,” and the numbers 0 through 12, in increments of 3, are indicated. Five points, labeled V, U, T, S, and R, are indicated along the curve. The curve begins at point V at point with coordinates 0 comma 12, and slants downward and to the right. It passes through point U at the point with coordinates 6 comma 9, point T at the point with coordinates 12 comma 6, point S at the point with coordinates 18 comma 3, and it ends at point R at the point with coordinates 24 comma 0.\" height=\"250\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR596879.g03.svg\" width=\"427\"></div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Combination T is allocatively efficient because customers will consume both donuts and cups of coffee.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Combination V is allocatively efficient because Deetopia has an absolute advantage in producing cups of coffee.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The opportunity cost of producing <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> cup of coffee is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> donuts.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The opportunity cost of producing <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> cup of coffee is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"6\"><math alttext=\"6\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> donuts.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The opportunity cost of producing <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> donut increases as more cups of coffee are produced.</p>"],"answer":2}]